⁠⁠👆

Learn how stress, placebo's and religion affect your brain & body with Dr. Emeran Mayer EP 1139 in today’s episode! @emeranmayer  ⁠⁠
In this episode we discuss:
* The biggest triggers for inflammation.⁠⁠
* The foods we should eat & avoid to improve our gut health.⁠⁠
* Why we’ve become so addicted to sugar & the effects it has on our body.⁠⁠
* Whether our brain or gut health affects our body more.⁠⁠
* How our digestive system functions.⁠⁠
* And so much more!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
🎙️Check out the episode now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link in bio!

2️⃣0️⃣ Congrats to @djokernole on 20 Grand Slam titles! #Wimbledon ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
🎾 Today, we’re bringing back one of my favorite interviews from the past with Novak Djokovic. He is currently ranked as world No. 1 by the Association of Tennis Professionals. Djokovic has been No. 1 for a record of over 320 weeks. I felt very inspired this last week as I watched him win his 20th Grand Slam title in Wimbledon and wanted to reflect back on our conversation from 2017. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
🏆 In this episode we discuss:⁠⁠
* How Novak started playing tennis & persevered through a traumatic childhood.⁠⁠
* How Novak recovered from his lowest point.⁠⁠
* How to understand the power of the mind to build a champion mindset.⁠⁠
* What love means to Novak and why it’s so important for him.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
☝️ Become #1 at your craft and build a CHAMPION’S mindset with #1 TENNIS CHAMPION in the world, Novak Djokovic on episode 1137! ⁠⁠

node.text:
Greatness is not about what you can accomplish, rather what pain and fear you can overcome and how you use your gifts to contribute to others.  Leave a “Yes” if you agree 🙏

In this journey of life we will face many obstacles. And if we aren’t “seeking discomfort” as the Yes Theory crew says, then pain will find it’s way to us eventually. 

6 months ago I took on a new challenge with boxing. I found the best trainer in @tony_jeffries who pushes me to my limits each week. 

I was goofy, uncoordinated, out of shape and a total beginner experiencing discomfort and pain in ever session. 

Instead of avoiding these experiences, I believe we should run toward them. 

Whatever you are afraid of, insecure about or worried how you will be viewed by others with embarrassment… those are the exact things you should look to embrace. 

Share below if you agree and what new challenge you are taking on to improve your overall growth. 

Shout out to @lobo__films for filling and this sick edit and @jonbrandoncruz for the inspiration and connection. 

#HeartAndGrind #mindsetofgreatness #greatness #boxing #inspirationalquotes #motivationalquotes #growthmindset

⁠⁠
🎾 Today, we’re bringing back one of my favorite interviews from the past with Novak Djokovic. He is currently ranked as world No. 1 by the Association of Tennis Professionals. Djokovic has been No. 1 for a record of over 320 weeks. I felt very inspired this last week as I watched him win his 20th Grand Slam title in Wimbledon and wanted to reflect back on our conversation from 2017. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
🏆 In this episode we discuss:⁠⁠
* How Novak started playing tennis & persevered through a traumatic childhood.⁠⁠
* How Novak recovered from his lowest point.⁠⁠
* How to understand the power of the mind to build a champion mindset.⁠⁠
* What love means to Novak and why it’s so important for him.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
☝️ Become #1 at your craft and build a CHAMPION’S mindset with #1 TENNIS CHAMPION in the world, Novak Djokovic on episode 1137! ⁠⁠

* Understanding the power of the mind and reaching your fullest potential with Wim Hof⁠⁠
* The science behind stress and how to manage it properly with Kelly McGonigal⁠⁠
* How to cope with feeling overwhelmed and get emotionally unstuck with Kati Morton⁠⁠
